subtitleNullable: wearable and smartphone data for sleep quality and behavioral health in youth
descriptionNullable:
Sleep Quality and Behavioral health of 24 university students collected using their smartwatches and smartphones for 7 consecutive days and nights.

Details can be found in the following papers

1. Arora, A., Chakraborty, P. and Bhatia, M.P.S., 2022, January. SleepQual and B. Health: Smartwatch and Smartphone based Behavioral Datasets of Youth. In 2022 12th International Conference on Cloud Computing, Data Science & Engineering (Confluence) (pp. 340-344). IEEE.
2. Arora, A., Chakraborty, P. and Bhatia, M.P.S., 2021. Intervention of Wearables and Smartphones in Real Time Monitoring of Sleep and Behavioral Health: An Assessment Using Adaptive Neuro-Fuzzy Technique. Arabian Journal for Science and Engineering, pp.1-26.
